{
  "text": "A previously unrecognized group 3 coronavirus isolated from turkeys with enteric disease was found to be genetically similar to IBV, a coronavirus that causes an upper-respiratory tract disease in chickens [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In this study, we determined the full-length genome sequence of 4 different TCoV strains and showed that the genomes were closely related to IBV except in the spike glycoprotein gene. All 4 strains of TCoV were found to be pathogenic for 1-day-old turkeys but were not pathogenic for 1-day-old chickens, indicating that the spike glycoprotein of this coronavirus was responsible for the host shift from chickens to turkeys and the pathogenicity shift from upper-respiratory disease to enteric disease.",
